.TH "dev_pm_opp_adjust_voltage" 9 "dev_pm_opp_adjust_voltage" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dev_pm_opp_adjust_voltage \- helper to change the voltage of an OPP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dev_pm_opp_adjust_voltage
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned long freq "  ","
.BI "unsigned long u_volt "  ","
.BI "unsigned long u_volt_min "  ","
.BI "unsigned long u_volt_max "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device for which we do this operation
.IP "freq" 12
OPP frequency to adjust voltage of
.IP "u_volt" 12
new OPP target voltage
.IP "u_volt_min" 12
new OPP min voltage
.IP "u_volt_max" 12
new OPP max voltage
.SH "RETURN"
-EINVAL for bad pointers, -ENOMEM if no memory available for the
copy operation, returns 0 if no modifcation was done OR modification was
successful.
